value.value: A groove on the mesopleuron, extending ventrally from a pit under the base of the forewings and, when complete, reaching the anteroventral margin of the metathorax.
The episternum that is located on the mesopleuron.
The basalare that is located in the mesothorax.
The acetabulum that is located posteroventrally on the mesopectus, accommodates the mesocoxa and is delimited anterolaterally by the postpectal carina.
The mesosubalare muscle that arises from the mesocoxa and inserts on the mesosubalare.
The discrimen that is located in the mesothorax and corresponds with the mesodiscrimenal lamella.
The discrimenal lamella that is located in the mesothorax.
The furca that is not paired, arises from the mesopectus and continuous with the mesodiscrimenal lamella.
The apodeme that connects the lateral mesofurcal arms and corresponds to the site of origin of the dorsal mesofurco-profurcal muscle.
The furcal pit that is located in the mesothorax.
The mesocoxal muscle that originates from the mesofurca and inserts on the mesocoxa.
The mesolaterophragmal muscle that arises from the mesofurca and inserts on the mesolaterophragma.
The metabasalar muscle that originates from the mesofurca and inserts on the metabasalare.
The sulcus that crosses the mesometapleuron from the posterolateral margin of the mesocoxal foramen to the mesopleural pit.
The line of separation that is located between the mesopectus and the metapectus.
The sclerite that is comprised of the fused meso- and metapleura.
The area that is limited anteriorly by the pronotum, laterally by the basalare, axillary sclerites, subalare and the mesopectus and posterolaterally by the mesopostnotum and the metanotum.

The sclerite that is U-shaped in cross section, connected anteriorly with the pronotum and the propectus, dorsally with the basalare, the mesonotum, the second axillary sclerite and the subalare, posteriorly with the metapectus and bears the mesodiscrimenal lamella and the mesofurca.

The phragma that extends along the ventral (posterior) margin of the ventral mesopostnotal flange and corresponds to the site of origin of the prophragmo-mesophragmal and the mesophragmo-metaphragmal muscles.
The carina that crosses the mesopleuron and limits ventrally the femoral depression.
The epicoxal sulcus that is located on the mesopleuron.
The area that is limited dorsally by the subalar ridge, posteroventrally by the speculum and ends posteriorly in the subalar pit.
The mesobasalar muscle that originates anteroventrally from the mesopleuron and insert on the mesobasalare.
The mesocoxal muscle that arises from the mesopleuron and inserts on the mesocoxa.

label.value: mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle

value.value: The hind wing third axillary muscle that arises from the mesopleuron and inserts on the third axillary sclerite of hind wing.
The area that is located laterally of the mesodiscrimen.
The sclerite that bears the mesophragma and the mesolaterophragma.
The area that is located posteromedially on the  mesoscutellum, is delimited anteriorly by the posterior scutellar depression.
The sulcus that extends medially along the parascutal carina and corresponds to a shallow ridge.

The sulcus that extends along the anterior margin of the mesoscutum between the anterior-most point of the preaxilla and the anteroadmedian line and corresponds to the vertical lobe of the mesoscutum.
The area that is located posteriorly of the transscutal line and is composed of the axillae and the mesoscutellum.
The metanotal muscle that arises from the mesonotum and inserts on the metanotum.
The scutellum that is located on the mesonotum.
The scutum that is located on the mesonotum.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the prothorax, mesothorax and the metapectal-propodeal complex.
The metafurcal muscle that arises from the mesospinasternum and inserts on the metafurca.
The mesocoxal muscle that originates at least partly from the mesodiscrimenal lamella and inserts on the mesocoxa.
The procoxal muscle that arises anteriorly from the mesodiscrimenal lamella and inserts posteriorly on the procoxa.
The eusternum that is located in the mesothorax.
The subalare that is located in the mesothorax.
The spiracle that is located on the border of the pronotum and mesopleuron.
The thoracic segment that is located between the prothorax and the metathorax and is delimited by the mesopectus and the mesonotum.
The trochantin that is located in the mesothorax.
The basalare that is located in the metathorax.
The coxa that is located on the hind leg.
The acetabulum that is concave, is located ventrally on metapectal-propodeal complex and is delimited anteriorly by the transverse metepisternal carina and accommodates the base of the metacoxa.
The metasubalare muscle that arises from the metacoxa and inserts on the metasubalare.
The discrimen that is located in the metathorax and corresponds to the metadiscrimenal lamella.
The discrimenal lamella that is located in the metathorax.
The furca that is located medioventrally on the metapectus.
